{"title_page": "Rev (company)", "text_new": "{{short description|transcription service and company}}\n{{Use American English|date=November 2019}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=November 2019}}\n{{Infobox company\n| name = Rev\n| logo = \n| type = \n| industry = [[Transcription (service)|Transcription]]\n| fate = \n| predecessor = <!-- or: | predecessors = -->\n| successor = <!-- or: | successors = -->\n| founded = 2010<!-- if known: {{Start date and age|YYYY|MM|DD}} in [[city]], country -->\n| founder = <!-- or: | founders = -->\n| defunct = <!-- {{End date|YYYY|MM|DD}} -->\n| hq_location_city = \n| hq_location_country = \n| area_served = <!-- or: | areas_served = -->\n| key_people = \n| products = \n| owner = <!-- or: | owners = -->\n| num_employees = \n| num_employees_year = <!-- Year of num_employees data (if known) -->\n| parent = \n| website = {{URL|rev.com}}\n}}\n\n'''Rev''' is a [[closed captioning]], [[subtitles]], and [[transcription service]]. The company, based in [[San Francisco]] and [[Austin]], was founded in 2010 and raised  million in funding. Its 50,000 independent contract workers transcribe audio for a per-minute rate. The service is used by major companies including [[Amazon (company)|Amazon]] and [[Microsoft]].{{r|Verge feature}} ''[[PC Magazine]]'' named the service an \"Editor's Choice\" in 2018,<ref>{{Cite web |last1=Moore |first1=Ben |title=Rev |work=[[PC Magazine]] |date=2018-06-28 |url=https://www.pcmag.com/review/358914/rev |language=en |accessdate=2019-11-26 |df=mdy-all }}</ref> and ranked it as the best transcription service in 2019.<ref>{{Cite web |last1=Moore |first1=Ben |title=The Best Transcription Services for 2019 |work=[[PC Magazine]] |date=2018-08-22 |url=https://www.pcmag.com/roundup/359079/the-best-transcription-services |language=en |accessdate=2019-11-26 |df=mdy-all }}</ref> The company received press in November 2019 for lowering its base transcription pay rate from 45 cents per transcribed minute to 30 cents.<ref name=\"Verge feature\">{{Cite web |last1=Deahl |first1=Dani |title=Rev transcribers hate the low pay, but the disturbing recordings are even worse |work=[[The Verge]] |date=2019-11-25 |url=https://www.theverge.com/2019/11/25/20979249/rev-recordings-transcriptions-low-pay-complaints-freelance-transcribers |language=en |accessdate=2019-11-26 |df=mdy-all }}</ref> Rev popularized itself on its rate pricing of {{usd|1}} per minute of transcribed audio. In 2020, Rev raised its rate to $1.25. The company predicted that the number of jobs per transcriber would not decrease and that transcribers would be paid more for \"harder jobs\".<ref>{{Cite web |last1=Statt |first1=Nick |title=Transcription service Rev is raising prices for the first time to $1.25 a minute |work=[[The Verge]] |date=2020-01-23 |url=https://www.theverge.com/2020/1/23/21079408/rev-transcription-service-price-raise |language=en |accessdate=2020-01-25 |df=mdy-all }}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n\n{{reflist}}\n\n== Further reading ==\n\n{{refbegin}}\n\n* {{Cite web |last1=McKay |first1=Tom |title=Report: Rev Asked Workers to Transcribe Audio Involving Sexual Assault, Child Abuse Without Warning |work=[[Gizmodo]] |date=2019-11-22 |url=https://gizmodo.com/report-rev-asked-workers-to-transcribe-audio-involving-1840007469 |language=en-us |accessdate=2019-11-26 |df=mdy-all }}\n* {{Cite web |last1=Menegus |first1=Bryan |title=Rev CEO: 'We Got a Few Things Wrong' |work=[[Gizmodo]] |date=2019-11-14 |url=https://gizmodo.com/rev-ceo-we-got-a-few-things-wrong-1839871943 |language=en-us |accessdate=2019-11-26 |df=mdy-all }}\n* {{Cite web |last1=Menegus |first1=Bryan |title=Transcription Platform Rev Slashes Minimum Pay for Workers |work=[[Gizmodo]] |date=2019-11-11 |url=https://gizmodo.com/transcription-platform-rev-slashes-minimum-pay-for-work-1839784941 |language=en-us |accessdate=2019-11-26 |df=mdy-all }}\n* {{Cite web |last1=Perez |first1=Sarah |title=Founded By Early oDesk Employees, Freelancer Marketplace Rev.com Raises  Million Series A |work=[[TechCrunch]] |date=2013-03-26 |url=http://social.techcrunch.com/2013/03/26/founded-by-early-odesk-employees-freelancer-marketplace-rev-com-raises-4-5-million-series-a/ |language=en-US |accessdate=2019-11-26 |df=mdy-all }}\n\n{{refend}}\n\n== External links ==\n\n* {{official website|https://www.rev.com/}}\n{{Transcription-Website-stub}}\n\n{{Portal bar|Companies}}\n\n[[Category:American companies established in 2010]]\n[[Category:Transcription services]]\n[[Category:Companies based in San Francisco]]\n[[Category:Companies based in Austin, Texas]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|transcription service and company}}\n{{Use American English|date=November 2019}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=November 2019}}\n{{Infobox company\n| name = Rev\n| logo = \n| type = \n| industry = [[Transcription (service)|Transcription]]\n| fate = \n| predecessor = <!-- or: | predecessors = -->\n| successor = <!-- or: | successors = -->\n| founded = 2010<!-- if known: {{Start date and age|YYYY|MM|DD}} in [[city]], country -->\n| founder = <!-- or: | founders = -->\n| defunct = <!-- {{End date|YYYY|MM|DD}} -->\n| hq_location_city = \n| hq_location_country = \n| area_served = <!-- or: | areas_served = -->\n| key_people = \n| products = \n| owner = <!-- or: | owners = -->\n| num_employees = \n| num_employees_year = <!-- Year of num_employees data (if known) -->\n| parent = \n| website = {{URL|rev.com}}\n}}\n\n'''Rev''' is a [[transcription service]]. The company, based in San Francisco and Austin, was founded in 2010 and raised  million in funding. Its 50,000 independent contract workers transcribe audio for a rate of  per minute. The service is used by major companies including Amazon and Microsoft.{{r|Verge feature}} ''[[PC Magazine]]'' named the service an \"Editor's Choice\" in 2018,<ref>{{Cite web |last1=Moore |first1=Ben |title=Rev |work=[[PC Magazine]] |date=2018-06-28 |url=https://www.pcmag.com/review/358914/rev |language=en |accessdate=2019-11-26 |df=mdy-all }}</ref> and ranked