{"title_page": "War on terror", "text_new": "{{pp-pc1}}\n{{About|the international military campaign}}\n{{Multiple issues|{{Update|date=April 2019}}\n{{POV title|date=June 2019}}\n{{Cleanup|reason=Multiple theaters are described yet none are particularly detailed and definitions of terrorism related activities must be tightened up.|date=July 2019}} }}\n{{Short description|International military campaign that started after the 11 September 2001 attacks}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2019}}\n{{Infobox military conflict\n| conflict    = War on terror\n| image       = [[File:War on Terror montage1.png|border|300px|alt='''Clockwise from top left:''' Aftermath of the [[September 11 attacks|11 September attacks]]; American infantry in [[Afghanistan]]; an American soldier and Afghan interpreter in [[Zabul Province]], Afghanistan; explosion of an Iraqi car bomb in [[Baghdad]]]]\n| caption     = '''Clockwise from top left:''' Aftermath of the [[September 11 attacks]]; American infantry in [[Afghanistan]]; an American soldier and Afghan interpreter in [[Zabul Province]], Afghanistan; explosion of an Iraqi car bomb in [[Baghdad]].\n| date        = [[September 11 attacks|11 September 2001]] \u2013 present{{refn|Origins date back to the 1980s.|group=note}}{{refn|The main phase occurs between 7 October 2001 and 31 December 2016|group=note}}<br />{{small|({{Age in years, months, weeks and days|month1=9|day1=11|year1=2001}})}}\n| place       = Global\n| cause       = [[September 11 attacks]]\n| status      = [[List of ongoing armed conflicts|Ongoing]]\n\n'''[[Al-Qaeda insurgency in Yemen]]''' (since 1998):{{refn|Origins date back to the 1980s.|group=note}}\n* Drone strikes being conducted by U.S.\n* [[Al-Qaeda]] Emirate in Yemen is declared on 31 March 2011\n* Insurgency escalates into a [[Yemeni Civil War (2015\u2013present)|full-scale civil war in 2015]]\n'''[[War in Afghanistan (2001\u2013present)|American-led intervention]] in [[War in Afghanistan (1978\u2013present)|Afghanistan]]''' (since 2001):\n* Fall of the [[Taliban]] government in Afghanistan\n* Destruction of [[al-Qaeda]] camps\n* [[Taliban insurgency]]\n** Initiation of [[Resolute Support Mission|Operation Resolute Support]] by [[NATO]]\n** Transfer of combat roles to [[Afghan Armed Forces]]\n** [[U.S.\u2013Afghanistan Strategic Partnership Agreement]]\n'''[[Iraqi conflict]]''' (since 2003):\n* [[Iraq War|Iraq War (2003\u201311)]]\n** Overthrow of the [[Ba'ath Party (Iraqi-dominated faction)|Ba'ath Party]] government in Iraq\n** [[Execution of Saddam Hussein]]\n** Death of [[Abu Musab al-Zarqawi]] in June 2006\n** [[Elections in Iraq|Free elections]]\n* [[Iraqi insurgency (post-U.S. withdrawal)|Iraqi insurgency (2011\u201314)]]\n* [[Iraqi Civil War (2014\u20132017)|Civil war (2014\u201317)]]\n* [[Iraqi insurgency (2017\u2013present)|Continued insurgency]]\n'''[[Insurgency in Khyber Pakhtunkhwa]]''' (2004-17):\n* low-level insurgency<ref>{{cite web|url=https://propakistani.pk/2018/04/24/terrorism-in-pakistan-declines-by-89-in-8-years/|title=Terrorism in Pakistan Declines by 89% in 8 Years|date=24 April 2018|work=Pro Pakistani}}</ref>\n* Elimination of [[Tehrik-i-Taliban Pakistan]], Al-Qaeda, Haqqani Network and other terrorist groups presence in Pakistan<ref>{{cite web|url=https://en.dailypakistan.com.pk/headline/us-senators-visit-south-waziristan-laud-pakistan-armys-efforts-in-dismantling-terrorist-networks/|title=US senators visit South Waziristan, laud Pakistan army's efforts in dismantling terrorist networks|date=3 July 2017|work=Daily Pakistan}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.dawn.com/news/1342961|title=US senators visit South Waziristan, praise advances made by military|date=3 July 2017|work=Dawn News}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://tribune.com.pk/story/786641/us-commander-commends-zarb-e-azb-for-disrupting-haqqani-networks-ability-to-target-afghanistan/|title=US commander commends Zarb-e-Azb for disrupting Haqqani network's ability to target Afghanistan|date=6 November 2014|work=Express Tribune|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141106165357/http://tribune.com.pk/story/786641/us-commander-commends-zarb-e-azb-for-disrupting-haqqani-networks-ability-to-target-afghanistan/|archive-date=6 November 2014|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n* Large number of terrorists killed while some fled to Afghanistan<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.voanews.com/a/us-drone-kills-afghan-based-pakistani-taliban-commander/4467419.html|title=US Drone Kills Afghan-Based Pakistani Taliban Commander|date=4 July 2018|work=Voice of America (VOA)}}</ref>\n* [[Death of Osama bin Laden|Killing of Osama bin Laden]]\n* Drone strikes  conducted by the [[Central Intelligence Agency|CIA]] till 2018 \n'''[[Military intervention against ISIL|International campaign against ISIL]]''' (since 2014):\n* [[Operation Inherent Resolve]]: U.S.-led Coalition airstrikes on ISIL positions in [[American-led intervention in Iraq (2014\u2013present)|Iraq]], [[American-led intervention in Syria|Syria]], [[2015 Egyptian military intervention in Libya|Egyptian airstrikes in Libya]], and [[Boko Haram insurgency|West African airstrikes in Nigeria]]\n* Multinational humanitarian effort\n* Arming and support for local ground forces\n* [[ISIL beheading incidents|ISIL beheadings]]<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.thedailybeast.com/articles/2014/08/21/obama-readies-for-war-on-isis.html|title=Obama vs ISIS: This time it's personal|date=22 August 2014|accessdate=9 September 2014|newspaper=The Daily Beast|last1=Lake|first1=Eli}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2014/08/23/world/middleeast/obama-adviser-says-military-action-possible-against-isis.html|title=U.S. weighs direct military action against ISIS in Syria|date=22 August 2014|accessdate=9 September 2014|work=The New York Times|first1=Peter|last1=Baker|first2=Michael D.|last2=Shear}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-europe-29360788|title=French hostage beheading: France to boost Syria rebels|publisher=BBC News|accessdate=28 September 2014|date=25 September 2014}}</ref><ref name=\"The Huffington Post\">{{cite news|url=https://www.huffingtonpost.com/2014/12/01/william-henderson-oil-worker-killed_n_6246202.html|title=Islamic State Allies In Egypt Say They Killed American Oil Worker William Henderson|work=The Huffington Post|accessdate=6 December 2014|date=1 December 2014}}</ref><ref name=BBCKassig1>{{cite news|title=Islamic State Kassig murder: Western jihadists probed|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-middle-east-30080874|accessdate=17 November 2014|publisher=BBC News|date=17 November 2014}}</ref><ref>[http://america.aljazeera.com/articles/2015/2/10/kayler-mueller-american-isil-hostage-is-dead.html \"Kayla Mueller, American ISIL hostage, is dead\"], [[Al Jazeera America]], 10 February 2015</ref><ref name=\"Egypt retaliates for the killings of 21 Egyptians\">{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-middle-east-31483631|agency=BBC News|title=Egypt 'bombs IS in Libya' after beheadings video|date=16 February 2015|accessdate=16 February 2015}}</ref>\n* ISIL defeated in Iraq in December 2017\n* ISIL defeated in Syria in March 2019 following the [[Battle of Baghuz Fawqani]]\n* [[Barisha raid|Death]] of ISIL leader [[Abu Bakr al-Baghdadi]]\n'''Other:'''\n* [[Operation Enduring Freedom \u2013 Horn of Africa|OEF Horn of Africa]]\n* [[Operation Enduring Freedom \u2013 Philippines|OEF Philippines]]\n* [[Operation Enduring Freedom \u2013 Trans Sahara|OEF Trans Sahara]]\n* [[Operation Enduring Freedom \u2013 Caribbean and Central America|OEF Caribbean and Central America]]\n| combatant1  = '''Co-Belligerent States'''\n* {{flag|United States}}\n* {{flag|United Kingdom}}\n* {{flag|France}}\n* {{flag|Russia}}\n----\n{{collapsible list\n| bullets = yes\n| title = '''Other {{flag|NATO}} members'''\n| titlestyle = background:transparent;text-align:left;font-weight:normal;\n| {{flag|Albania}}\n| {{flag|Belgium}}\n| {{flag|Bulgaria}}\n| {{flag|Canada}}\n| {{flag|Croatia}}